}{}\begin{equation*} \frac{{{\rm raw\;DGE}}}{{{\rm informative\;reads \cdot length\;of\;interval}}} \cdot 10^{11} ({\rm vlincRNAs}) \end{equation*}\end{document}
where ‘informative reads’ is the total number of reads in the sample uniquely aligning to the reference genome and corresponding to chr1–22, X,Y; ‘length of interval’ is the length of vlincRNA reduced by total length of overlapping UCSC Genes exons and rRNA repeats in case of vlincRNA or sum of lengths of exons in case of UCSC Genes transcripts.
